\f1\fs20\cf0\b\ltrpar\qr\sb60\sa0\li0\ri0 (Total 1 mark)\par
\f1\fs27\cf1\ltrpar\ql\sb450\sa45\li150\ri45 Q2.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li567\ri567 Many computerised cipher systems use asymmetric encryption methods to resolve the key exchange problem that is associated with symmetric ciphers, such as the Vernam and Caesar ciphers.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 Explain what the key exchange problem is, in relation to a symmetric cipher.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 _______________________________________________________________________\par
