\f1\fs27\cf1\ltrpar\ql\sb450\sa45\li150\ri45 Q3.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li567\ri567 A message is to be transmitted from computer A to computer B. The message will be encrypted using asymmetric encryption. To enable computer B to authenticate that the message was sent by computer A, a digital signature will also be sent with the message.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 Explain how computer B will decrypt the message and verify that it was sent by computer A.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 In your response you should refer to the specific keys that will be used in this process.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 You do \b not\b0  need to explain how computer A will encrypt the message or create the digital signature.\par
