\f1\fs27\cf1\ltrpar\ql\sb450\sa45\li150\ri45 Q6.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li567\ri567 Between 2008 and 2010, a company that was gathering data for an online mapping system, using cars fitted with cameras and WiFi equipment, collected some information that was being transmitted on personal WiFi networks. The company apologised for doing this and an investigation found that a small number of software developers had been responsible for adding this functionality to the mapping system data collection software.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 In the context of this example, discuss:\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~how it was possible for this data to be collected.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~what steps the owners of the networks could have taken to prevent the data from being collected.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~what legal and ethical issues might have arisen as a result of collecting this data.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~what lessons the company might have learnt from the incident and how their practices might have changed as a result of it.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567\fi0 In your answer you will be assessed on your ability to follow a line of reasoning to produce a coherent, relevant and structured response.\par
\f1\fs20\cf0\b\ltrpar\qr\sb60\sa0\li0\ri0 (Total 12 marks)\par
}